oun + ばかり<br>        </p>    </div></td>    <td><p> one thing; nothing (little else) but one thing </p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="37" colspan="2"><p> Sometimes it expresses unfairness or bias.<br>Emphasizes the positive proposition of      a noun/pronoun. <br>        Replaceが、は、を with ばかり；add ばかり before or after other particles <br>    </p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="18"><div align="right">        <p align="right"> <span class="style2"><span class="style3"> 日本語<span class="style12">ばかり</span>勉強しました。<br>私はすし<span class="style12">ばかり</span>食べました。</span><span class="style3"><br>        </span></span></p>    </div></td>    <td height="18">I studied <span class="style12">only</span> Japanese <span class="style12">and        nothing else</span>. <br>I ate <span class="style12">only</span> Sushi <span class="style12">and nothingelse</span> (although there were many other things to eat).</td>  </tr></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table width="90%" border="1" align="center">  <tr>    <td width="48%" height="19" bgcolor="#CCCCCC">〜しか (particle) 〜ない</td>    <td width="52%" bgcolor="#cccccc"><p align="right">Yookoso I-450 </p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="37"><div align="right">        <p>  <span class="style14">Noun/pronoun</span> + しか 〜ない<br>        </p>    </div></td>    <td><p>only, nothing but <span class="style14">Noun/pronoun</span></p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="37" colspan="2"><p> Emphasizes the negative proposition of non-<span class="style14">Noun/pronoun</span><br>        Replaceが、は、を with しか；add しか  after other particles <br>    </p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="51"><div align="right">        <p align="right"> 日本語<span class="style16">しか</span>勉強<span class="style16">しません</span>でした。  <br>          <br>          私は毎日すし<span class="style16">しか</span>食べません。<span class="style2"><span class="style3"><br>        </span></span></p>    </div></td>    <td height="51"> I studied <span class="style16">nothing but </span> Japanese      <span class="style12">and this was not sufficient</span>. <br>      I eat <span class="style16">nothing but</span> Sushi everyday. </td>  </tr></table><p>&nbsp;</p><UL>	<LI>			<B>練習 (Practice Quizzes)</B><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Quiz: </LI></LI> 			 			<p align="center"><a href="#top">Return to Top</a> </p> 			<p align="center"><a href="../../../../glist.php">Ｒeturn to Grammar Lists</a></p>	  </UL>          </tr></table></BODY></HTML>